                    <span>Like C.G. Jung, I consider my I Ching, along with the Bible<br>and the Koran, one of the most important books I own.  It is<br>a holy book, and the Wilhelm/Baynes translation is the best.<br>I recommend it unreservedly to anyone seriously interested<br>in the ancient yet timeless Chinese view of the cosmos.</span>
                  
              
